page.title: 08Buildings 1 Giggleswick P.
page.content: Farther Rome with its barns is a C17th. Grade 2 listed building. It is a two-storey building with dripstone running the full length of the ground floor windows and a stepped up over door, above which is a sundial panel. The door has a simple moulded door head with initials A.C.V., dated 1690. Field Gate is a C17th.,two -storey building with its back to the road. There is a good door with mouldings and a decorated headdate with initials and the date1684 (see slide C). The back door has chamfered jambs and a simple ornamented head.
